"use strict";(self.webpackChunkmina=self.webpackChunkmina||[]).push([[948],{2394:function(e){e.exports=JSON.parse('{"blogPosts":[{"id":"french-take-two","metadata":{"permalink":"/mina/blog/french-take-two","editUrl":"https://github.com/xh313/mina/blog/2022-06-11-french-take-two.md","source":"@site/blog/2022-06-11-french-take-two.md","title":"French Take 2...","description":"J\'ai finalement chang\xe9 la langue de mon t\xe9l\xe9phone du finnois au fran\xe7ais apr\xe8s un an... // I finally changed my phone language from Finnish to French after a year...","date":"2022-06-11T00:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"June 11, 2022","tags":[{"label":"French","permalink":"/mina/blog/tags/french"},{"label":"English","permalink":"/mina/blog/tags/english"}],"readingTime":0.875,"truncated":true,"authors":[{"name":"Xuehuai","title":"Student at Pomona College","url":"https://xh313.user.srcf.net/","imageURL":"https://github.com/xh313.png","key":"xh313"}],"nextItem":{"title":"Diary in Rovaniemi \ud83d\ude44","permalink":"/mina/blog/paivakirja-rovaniemella"}},"content":"J\'ai finalement chang\xe9 la langue de mon t\xe9l\xe9phone du finnois au fran\xe7ais apr\xe8s un an... // I finally changed my phone language from Finnish to French after a year...\\n\\n\x3c!--truncate--\x3e\\n\\n## En Fran\xe7ais\\n\\nJ\'ai finalement chang\xe9 la langue de mon t\xe9l\xe9phone du finnois au fran\xe7ais apr\xe8s un an. J\'esp\xe8re que je n\'oublierai pas le finnois, mais je dois vraiment commencer \xe0 rafra\xeechir mon fran\xe7ais si je ne veux pas \xe9chouer \xe0 mon cours de fran\xe7ais le semestre prochain \ud83e\udd72\\n\\nSi vous souhaitez savoir comment se d\xe9roule mon apprentissage du fran\xe7ais et en quoi il est diff\xe9rent de celui du finnois, consultez mon blogue linguistique !\\n\\n## In English (DeepL translated)\\nI finally changed my phone language from Finnish to French after a year. I hope I won\'t forget Finnish, but I really need to start brushing up on my French if I don\'t want to fail my French class next semester \ud83e\udd72\\n\\nIf you want to know how my French learning is going and how it is different from Finnish, check out my language blog!"},{"id":"paivakirja-rovaniemella","metadata":{"permalink":"/mina/blog/paivakirja-rovaniemella","editUrl":"https://github.com/xh313/mina/blog/2022-03-18-paivakirja-rovaniemella/index.md","source":"@site/blog/2022-03-18-paivakirja-rovaniemella/index.md","title":"Diary in Rovaniemi \ud83d\ude44","description":"P\xe4iv\xe4kirja Rovaniemella \ud83d\ude44","date":"2022-03-18T00:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"March 18, 2022","tags":[{"label":"Finnish","permalink":"/mina/blog/tags/finnish"},{"label":"English","permalink":"/mina/blog/tags/english"}],"readingTime":1.925,"truncated":true,"authors":[{"name":"Xuehuai","title":"Student at Pomona College","url":"https://xh313.user.srcf.net/","imageURL":"https://github.com/xh313.png","key":"xh313"}],"prevItem":{"title":"French Take 2...","permalink":"/mina/blog/french-take-two"},"nextItem":{"title":"The 5th month studying Finnish","permalink":"/mina/blog/viides-kuukausi"}},"content":"P\xe4iv\xe4kirja Rovaniemella \ud83d\ude44\\n## Suomeksi\\n\\nRovaniemen Ruokasenkadulla ei ole ollenkaan ruokaa (vaan hautauspalvelua, tietenkin), ja kaaduin kadulla j\xe4\xe4ss\xe4 5 kertaa p\xe4iv\xe4ss\xe4.\\n![Hautauspalvelut](./hautauspalvelut.jpg)\\n> Hautauspalvelut Ruokasenkadulla.\\n\\n\x3c!--truncate--\x3e\\nMutta mielest\xe4ni mukaan, Rovaniemi oli muutakin kuin tylsyytt\xe4. Ainakin ei kukaan en\xe4\xe4 vastannut englanniksi kun aloitin vuoropuheluja suomeksi. Sen takia olen oppinut yht\xe4 paljon suomea kuin olen kaatunut lumessa. Mutta, kaikki puhuikin suomea kaverini kanssa, ja he eiv\xe4t pystynyt ymm\xe4rt\xe4m\xe4\xe4n mit\xe4\xe4n kuitenkin.\\n\\nJoulupukkia tai revontulia ei ollenkaan n\xe4y. Vain k\xe4yn taidemuseossa katsomassa, koska yksi kadulla olevien matkustajista suositteli. Mutta mieleni harhaili kuin kuvassa (tulossa l\xf6ytyy).\\n\\nSitten menimme m\xe4keen, jolla oli paljon lunta. Allen teki lumiukon, ja sitten vahvasti potkii sen p\xe4\xe4h\xe4n. En tied\xe4 mit\xe4 saan ajatella t\xe4st\xe4.\\n\\n![Potkaistu lumiukko](./lumiukko.jpg)\\n> Allen potkaisi lumiukon.\\n\\nEn tied\xe4 miksi maksoin melkein puoli budjetistani k\xe4yd\xe4 t\xe4ss\xe4. Se sai minut kysym\xe4\xe4n itselt\xe4 el\xe4m\xe4st\xe4ni. Nyt odotan lennon takaisin Helsinkiin, ja ajattelen, ett\xe4 eilen Rovaniemell\xe4 vain oli totaalista outoa unta. No, ehk\xe4 on my\xf6s el\xe4myst\xe4. En ole varma.\\n\\n## In English\\n**Diary in Rovaniemi. \ud83d\ude44**\\n\\nThere is no food at all on Ruokasenkatu (\u2018Foody street\u2019 if I literally interpret it) in Rovaniemi (but only a funeral service, of course), and I fell on icy streets 5 times a day.\\n\\nBut I think Rovaniemi wasn\u2019t quite just boring. At least nobody answered in English anymore when I started dialogues in Finnish. As a result, I have learned as much Finnish as I have fallen in the snow. But everyone spoke Finnish with my friends too, and they couldn\'t understand anything anyway.\\nThere was no Santa Claus or northern lights at all. I only went to check out the art museum because one of the random passengers on the street recommended it. But my mind wandered as in the picture.\\n\\n![Mieleni harhaili](./harhailla.jpg)\\n> Mieleni harhaili taidemuseossa.\\n\\nThen we went to a hill with a lot of snow on it. Allen made a snowman, and then brutally kicked it in the head. I don\'t know what to make of this.\\n![Potkaistu lumiukko](./lumiukko.jpg)\\n> Allen kicking the snowman.\\n\\nI don\'t know why I spent almost half my budget to visit this place. It made me question myself about my life. Now waiting for my flight back to Helsinki, I\'m thinking that yesterday in Rovaniemi was just an absolutely weird dream. Well, maybe there is an experience too. I\'m not sure."},{"id":"viides-kuukausi","metadata":{"permalink":"/mina/blog/viides-kuukausi","editUrl":"https://github.com/xh313/mina/blog/2021-11-03-viides-kuukausi.md","source":"@site/blog/2021-11-03-viides-kuukausi.md","title":"The 5th month studying Finnish","description":"Suomeksi","date":"2021-11-03T00:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"November 3, 2021","tags":[{"label":"Finnish","permalink":"/mina/blog/tags/finnish"},{"label":"English","permalink":"/mina/blog/tags/english"}],"readingTime":0.805,"truncated":true,"authors":[{"name":"Xuehuai","title":"Student at Pomona College","url":"https://xh313.user.srcf.net/","imageURL":"https://github.com/xh313.png","key":"xh313"}],"prevItem":{"title":"Diary in Rovaniemi \ud83d\ude44","permalink":"/mina/blog/paivakirja-rovaniemella"},"nextItem":{"title":"Is Chinese or Japanese harder to learn for Finnish speakers?","permalink":"/mina/blog/quora-ans-cn-jp"}},"content":"## Suomeksi\\nT\xe4n\xe4\xe4n on sattumalta viides kuukausi siit\xe4, kun aloitin suomea opiskelun, mutta en edes ehdi juhlimiselle pieni hetki. Se on liian traaginen ja en pysty keskustelemaan en\xe4\xe4 sit\xe4.\\n\x3c!--truncate--\x3e\\nOlen palanut itseasiassa melkein loppuun itseni nykyisin ja en jaksa mit\xe4\xe4n. Kirjoitin v\xe4h\xe4n, koska se on ehk\xe4 erityinen p\xe4iv\xe4, vaikka olenhan viel\xe4 niin ep\xe4onnistunut t\xe4ss\xe4 kieless\xe4 ja minulla en ole vapaa oppimiselle kuitenkin. Puhun sit\xe4 yht\xe4 huonosti kuin paska, eli lopetan t\xe4h\xe4n.\\n\\n## In English\\nToday happens to be the fifth month since I started studying Finnish, but I don\'t even have a small moment to celebrate. It\'s too tragic and I can\'t discuss it anymore. I\'m actually almost burnt out on myself these days and I can\'t take anything. I wrote a bit because it is perhaps a special day, although I am still so unsuccessful in this language and I don\u2019t have free time for learning it anyway. I speak it as bad as shit, so I\'ll stop here."},{"id":"quora-ans-cn-jp","metadata":{"permalink":"/mina/blog/quora-ans-cn-jp","editUrl":"https://github.com/xh313/mina/blog/2021-09-23-quora-ans.md","source":"@site/blog/2021-09-23-quora-ans.md","title":"Is Chinese or Japanese harder to learn for Finnish speakers?","description":"Original post link here.","date":"2021-09-23T00:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"September 23, 2021","tags":[{"label":"Finnish","permalink":"/mina/blog/tags/finnish"},{"label":"English","permalink":"/mina/blog/tags/english"},{"label":"Quora","permalink":"/mina/blog/tags/quora"}],"readingTime":3.51,"truncated":true,"authors":[{"name":"Xuehuai","title":"Student at Pomona College","url":"https://xh313.user.srcf.net/","imageURL":"https://github.com/xh313.png","key":"xh313"}],"prevItem":{"title":"The 5th month studying Finnish","permalink":"/mina/blog/viides-kuukausi"}},"content":"Original post link [here](https://qr.ae/pvHn6B).\\n\\n## Suomeksi\\n\xc4idinkieleni on kiina (mandarin) ja osaankin v\xe4h\xe4n japania (opettelin sit\xe4 noin 2 vuotta lapsuudessa mutta puhun viel\xe4 huonosti). Minun on vaikea vastata sinun kysymykseen, koska maailmassa ei ole varmasti helpompi kielt\xe4 kaikille. Se on tosi subjektiivinen aihe ja perustuu vahvasti siihen, ett\xe4 mik\xe4 \xe4idinkielesi on, ja sitten mitk\xe4 muita kieli\xe4 sin\xe4 voit puhua.\\n\x3c!--truncate--\x3e\\n\\nUNESCO julkaisi sijoitusta, jossa kirjoitetaan ett\xe4 japanin kieli on vaikeampi kuin kiinan englanninkieliselle (linkki on t\xe4\xe4ll\xe4: Language Difficulty Ranking - Effective Language Learning).\\n\\nMutta mielest\xe4ni t\xe4\xe4 ei ole v\xe4ltt\xe4m\xe4tt\xe4 totta suomenkieliselle, koska kuin opettelen suomea nykyisin, tajuan usein ett\xe4 japanin kieli on niin samanlainen kuin suomi. Ensinn\xe4, sanaa lausutaan samanlaisella tavalla suomeksi ja japaniksi, joissa on pitki\xe4 vokaaleja ja konsonantteja (esim. tuuli\u2260tuli, \u3061\u3087\u3063\u3068\u2260\u3061\u3087\u3068). Kiinan kielell\xe4 ei ole sit\xe4, mut on kuitenkin 4 toonia (esim. \u4e5fy\u011b\u2260\u53f6y\xe8\u2260\u7237y\xe9). Siksi tarvitset tehd\xe4 erityist\xe4 \u2019s\xe4velt\xe4\u2019 joka tavu kiinaksi, ja jos et viel\xe4 puhu tonaalisia kieli\xe4, saatat ajatella ett\xe4 se on eritt\xe4in vaikea\u2026\\n\\nSitten kieliopista\u2026 ajattelen ett\xe4 sek\xe4 suomen ett\xe4 japanin kieliopit ovat sekavat kiinankieliselle (mulle\u2026) koska sanojen loput ovat usein muokkaisi (esim. \u98df\u3079\u308b=yleiskielen \u2019sy\xf6d\xe4\u2019 ja puhekielen \u2019sy\xf6\u2019, \u98df\u3079\u307e\u3059=yleiskielen \u2019sy\xf6\u2019, \u98df\u3079\u307e\u3057\u305f=yleiskielen \u2019s\xf6i\u2019, \u98df\u3079\u305f\u3044=haluta sy\xf6d\xe4, \u98df\u3079\u3082\u306e=ruoka/sy\xf6t\xe4v\xe4, jne.). Kiinan kielell\xe4 ei ole taas sit\xe4, vaan paljon \u2019prepositions\u2019, jotka on ehk\xe4 my\xf6s hankala ymm\xe4rt\xe4\xe4 koska joskus en edes tied\xe4 my\xf6sk\xe4\xe4n miksi niill\xe4 tavoilla k\xe4ytet\xe4\xe4n n\xe4it\xe4 sanoja.\\n\\nMutta, kaikki on oma mielipiteeni ja tietysti opetella kiinaa jos sin\xe4 haluat tehd\xe4 niin!!! Se on niin kaunis kieli ja ei ole mahdoton oppia, vaikka se on erilainen kuin paljon kieli\xe4 maailmassa (n\xe4kee, suomen kielell\xe4 on sama tilanne!). Olen varma ett\xe4 aloitat tyk\xe4t\xe4 sit\xe4 kielt\xe4 jos yrit\xe4t ymm\xe4rt\xe4\xe4 sit\xe4 :) Japanin kieli on my\xf6s tosi mielenkiintoinen ja kannattaa kokeilla.\\nSuomen kieleni on viel\xe4 aika huono, anteeksi. Toivon, ett\xe4 t\xe4m\xe4 voi auttaa.\\n\\nOnnea!\\n\\n## In English\\nMy mother tongue is Chinese (Mandarin) and I know a little Japanese (I learned it for about 2 years as a child but I still speak it badly). It\'s hard for me to answer your question because there is certainly no easier language in the world for everyone. It\'s a really subjective topic and is strongly based on what your mother tongue is, and then what other languages you can speak.\\n\\nUNESCO published a ranking that says Japanese is more difficult than Chinese for English speakers (link here: Language Difficulty Ranking - Effective Language Learning).\\nBut I don\'t think this is necessarily true for a Finnish speaker, because as I\'m learning Finnish these days, I often realise that Japanese is so similar to Finnish. First of all, the word is pronounced in a similar way in Finnish and Japanese, which have long vowels and consonants (e.g. tuuli\u2260tuli, \u3061\u3087\u3063\u3068\u2260\u3061\u3087\u3068). Chinese does not have it, but there are 4 toons (e.g. \u4e5fy\u011b\u2260\u53f6y\xe8\u2260\u7237y\xe9). Therefore you need to make a special \'tone\' for each syllable in Chinese, and if you don\'t yet speak tonal languages, you might find it very difficult...\\n\\nThen about grammar... I think both Finnish and Japanese grammars are confusing for a Chinese speaker (me...) because the endings of words are often edited (e.g. \u98df\u3079\u308b=general language \'eat\' and colloquial \'eat\', \u98df\u3079\u307e\u3059=general language \'eat\', \u98df\u3079\u307e\u3057\u305f=general language \'ate\', \u98df\u3079\u305f\u3044=want to eat, \u98df\u3079\u3082\u306e=food/eating, etc.). Chinese again doesn\'t have that, but a lot of \'prepositions\', which may also be difficult to understand because sometimes I don\'t even know why those words are used in those ways either.\\n\\nBut, all is my opinion and of course learn Chinese if you want to do so!!! It is such a beautiful language and not impossible to learn, although it is different from a lot of languages in the world (you see, Finnish is the same situation!). I\'m sure you\'ll start to like the language if you try to understand it :) Japanese is also really interesting and worth a try.\\n\\nMy Finnish is still pretty bad, sorry. I hope this can help.\\n\\nGood luck!"}]}')}}]);